ainer X is running workflow Y\"\n    45→and collects status. The agent is self-directing.\n    46→\n    47→### cloche-agent (In-Container Runtime)\n    48→\n    49→Autonomous process running inside the Docker container. Responsibilities:\n    50→- Parse the workflow DSL (workflow files live in the codebase)\n    51→- Walk the workflow graph, executing steps and following results\n    52→- Invoke coding agents (Claude Code, custom commands) and scripts\n    53→- Stream structured status events back to `cloched`\n    54→- Run to completion (`done` or `abort`) without human intervention\n    55→\n    56→The agent is told which workflow to execute at launch. It handles everything else.\n    57→\n    58→## Communication\n    59→\n    60→### CLI <-> Daemon: gRPC\n    61→\n    62→- Protobuf contracts define the API (the API is the spec)\n    63→- Bidirectional streaming for `logs` (tail container output in real-time)\n    64→- Unix socket for local communication, TCP for remote\n    65→\n    66→### Agent <-> Daemon: Structured JSON over stdout\n    67→\n    68→- The agent writes JSON-lines to stdout with status updates\n    69→- `cloched` attaches to the container's stdout stream via Docker API\n    70→- Messages include: step started, step completed (with result name), logs, errors\n    71→- Kill/cancel: daemon sends SIGTERM to container, agent handles graceful shutdown\n    72→\n    73→## Workflow DSL\n    74→\n    75→### Vocabulary\n    76→\n    77→| Concept  | Description                                                        |\n    78→|----------|--------------------------------------------------------------------|\n    79→| workflow | A named graph of steps connected by result wiring                  |\n    80→| step     | A unit of work (type: `agent` or `script`)                         |\n    81→| result   | A named outcome reported by a step (e.g. \"success\", \"fail\")       |\n    82→| wiring   | Maps a step's result to the next step                              |\n    83→| done     | Built-in terminal step indicating successful completion            |\n    84→| abort    | Built-in terminal step indicating failure (reports error and exits)|\n    85→\n    86→### Syntax\n    87→\n    88→```\n    89→workflow \"implement-feature\" {\n    90→  step code {\n    91→    prompt = file(\"prompts/implement.md\")\n    92→    container {\n    93→      image = \"cloche/agent:latest\"\n    94→      network_allow = [\"docs.python.org\", \"internal-docs.company.com\"]\n    95→    }\n    96→    results = [success, fail, retry_with_feedback]\n    97→  }\n    98→\n    99→  step check {\n   100→    run = \"make test && make lint\""}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_016F7TzA1mS3EuWMqyz9Bth2","session_id":"a2c49b8d-da70-4500-b77a-712a3c934288","uuid":"199018ed-d871-470a-a5e4-9f8ddf018375","timestamp":"2026-03-17T14:11:17.520Z"}
